DataBase.Opration

Class Music

  • java.lang.Object
    • DataBase.Opration.Music
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Playable

    public class Music
extends java.lang.Object
implements Playable
    This is the music class, which holds the database properties, and provides functionality to creating and initializing a music object. It also implements the Playable interface, since this class should have access to a play(), stop(), pause() and next() function
